The article provides a compilation of statements from various sources about Judge Sonia Sotomayor, who was nominated by President Barack Obama to serve on the Supreme Court in 2009. The statements are from Republicans, Democrats, legal experts, law enforcement groups, business organizations, and others. The overall sentiment is positive, with many praising Sotomayor's qualifications, experience, intelligence, and fairness. Some highlight her background as a prosecutor and her ability to bring a fresh perspective to the bench. Others note her commitment to following the law and her balanced record on business and civil rights cases.